# Project Workflow

## 1. Overview

This document explains the operational workflow of the project.

The project has two complementary workflows:

1. **Document RAG workflow**
2. **Structured environmental workflow**

Together, they support evidence-based environmental screening using:

- MapBiomas;
- INPE / TerraBrasilis;
- document retrieval;
- municipality-year indicators;
- environmental risk scoring;
- cited RAG answers.

The system is designed to support analysts, not to replace human review or legal interpretation.

---

## 2. High-Level Workflow

```text
MapBiomas + INPE sources
        │
        ├── Document workflow
        │       ├── PDF documents
        │       ├── text extraction
        │       ├── text cleaning
        │       ├── chunking
        │       ├── embeddings
        │       ├── vector database
        │       └── RAG answers
        │
        └── Structured workflow
                ├── MapBiomas table
                ├── INPE / PRODES table
                ├── municipality-year panel
                ├── environmental indicators
                ├── risk score
                └── structured evidence
```

---

## 3. Document RAG Workflow

The document RAG workflow processes MapBiomas and INPE / TerraBrasilis documents so they can be retrieved by semantic search.

### 3.1 Input

Expected input folders:

```text
data/raw/mapbiomas/documents/
data/raw/inpe/documents/
```

Expected document types:

- technical reports;
- methodology documents;
- monitoring reports;
- source documentation;
- PDF files related to MapBiomas, INPE, TerraBrasilis or PRODES.

---

### 3.2 Step 1 — Parse PDF Documents

Module:

```text
src/agro_rag/processing/parse_pdf.py
```

Main function:

```python
parse_and_save_pdf_folder()
```

Purpose:

```text
PDF documents
→ page-level text table
```

Expected output:

```text
data/interim/parsed_documents/mapbiomas_pages.parquet
data/interim/parsed_documents/inpe_pages.parquet
```

Main fields:

| Field | Description |
|---|---|
| `source` | MapBiomas or INPE |
| `document_name` | Name of the document |
| `file_path` | Local file path |
| `page_number` | Page number extracted from the PDF |
| `year` | Reference year, when available |
| `theme` | Document theme |
| `language` | Document language |
| `text` | Extracted page text |
| `text_length` | Number of characters in the raw text |

---

### 3.3 Step 2 — Clean Extracted Text

Module:

```text
src/agro_rag/processing/clean_text.py
```

Main function:

```python
clean_parsed_pages()
```

Purpose:

```text
raw extracted text
→ cleaner retrieval-ready text
```

Cleaning includes:

- whitespace normalization;
- simple page artifact removal;
- broken hyphenation correction;
- removal of empty or very short pages.

Expected output:

```text
data/interim/parsed_documents/all_pages_clean.parquet
